#1 If someone doesn’t like you, ask them to lend you their pen. Or any  small favor. To justify their actions, they will then like you better. After that, they’ll also more likely to do you a second favor (“foot-in-the-door phenomenon”).

#2 Instead of saying “I know”. say “You’re right”
It makes you look less like an idiot and makes them feel smart, which makes them easier to work with.

#3 If you love someone for their looks, it’s Obsession.
If you love someone for their kindness, it’s admiration.
If you love someone for their money, it’s interest.
If you love someone because they love you, it’s empathy.
If you’re confused why you love this person, it’s definitely love.

#4 If someone is yelling at you just look in their eyes and say “Damn, all what they said about you is true.” They won’t say another word.
If you want to know if someone’s looking at you just yawn and they will yawn back.

#5 If a person won’t stop talking then drop something. This will throw the person off and they will realize how much and how long they have been talking.

All from me ;

Used to be very difficult for me to say “NO” to other people, even when it harmed me. .. Now I don’t think twice before I do it, but for some of you who need an easier and softer way here are some of the phrases I personally used to say …
.
#1 Sounds nice but I can not/ am not available.
.
#2 I am sorry that I can not help you right now.
.
#3 Sorry but I am not available right now ( if they ask why, you can explain or just cut them short that is personal , not everyone deserve an explanation)
.
#4 Sorry can not help you right now, maybe an other time.
.
#5 Unfortunately this is not a good time, so I will need to pass on this one, (sorry). You can choose to say sorry or no.
.
I specifically liked to use long forms of saying “NO” to different people for a better understanding and a stronger point, but also a short “No/nope” is just as effective 🙃.
.

Been living away from home since 17-18 years old and I do not mean different cities but states, and now…., now continent. 
Never claimed to be the easy going child even that I used to do what I was asked . But growing up made me realize that living your life in your own terms isn’t and should not be a break dealer to your loved ones. So crushing my father’s dream by quitting  medical school, going far changing continents, trying everything I can to reach my main goal atm which #financialfreedom💰  and creating my own happy family should not be a problem I feel guilty about. 
But that doesn’t mean I don’t want to see him happy, that’s why doing small stuff is important, it shows still connection 🤍.

I know it might just seem like a simple selfie and narcissistic at some point but it does not have that meaning to me, it is almost the end of 2023 and yet an other year that I have dealt with the doubts of the way how I look. 

Sometimes I forget that I was born different ( and trust me when I say I do embrace the sh*t out of it), but sometimes some shots are below the belt and I do admit it, those shots hurt as hell! 

So jumping back to the reason why this post, just a reminder to myself to not be afraid to show my face just because people do not read a book in their life! And to everyone there who is different as well, I want to say to CLAP BACK IF THEY DESERVE IT!

2023 from beginning to end was a ride so here are some bullet points!

* Moved in with a roommate which I thought was a good person, a fifty year old single mom of a 11 year old child.
*Broke up from my long distance relationship.
*Started to understand that she was a scammer and done wrong, after helping her get a house and landing $5k 
*Start fighting with her she wants me out of the house but can not do anything. 
*My uncle dies from cancer, have to go to USA, my ex-roommate take down my door by force and throws everything of mine out and steals $3k!
*Had to deal with school and work at the same time!
*Move in a new location! New roommates not any better but manageable!
*Start an internship to finish my co-op, working 6 months for free for a crap company!
*Trying to get myself out there, going to dates and getting to know people, nothing happen!
*August get my heart broken by a dumb date that I got love bombed and still missing my ex!
*September goes in an unexpected date end up in a relationship ❤️
*November get scammed $6k and discover that my ex-roommate had use y info to apply for credit cards and gotten one and putting me in a $2k with a bank. CALLS THE POLICE AND EVERYTHING, finally sort it out!
*December the police stop the investigations bc I do not have enough proof, work is loaded, my internship as well.

And those are just some highlights! This new year, is no space for errors! No more feeling bad for snakes and skan*s!
